Patient: I'm worried about my heart, what exercises can I do to help with my heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: Walking is a great start. Start slowly, then increase as you feel comfortable.

Patient: How long should I be walking for?

Healthcare Educator: Start with 10 minutes, gradually increase to at least 30 minutes, most days of the week.

Patient: Can I do any other exercises apart from walking?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, cycling or swimming are also good. But remember, always go at your own pace.

Patient: I feel tired easily, should I still exercise?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, but break it into smaller sessions. Rest when needed and don't push too hard.

Patient: Is it safe to lift weights?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, but use light weights. If you feel dizzy or breathless, stop immediately.